BLUETONGUE - EUROPE: ROMANIA (GORJ) CATTLE, SEROTYPE 4, OIE
************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 14 Jan 2021
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2021; 34(02) [edited]
https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?reportid=37607


Bluetongue [BTV], Romania
-------------------------
Information received [and dated] on 14 Jan 2021 from Dr. Robert Viorel Chioveanu, President, Secretary of State, Chief Veterinary Officer, Veterinary Services, National Sanitary Veterinary and Food Safety Authority, Bucharest, Romania

Summary
Report type: Follow-up report No 1
Date of start of the event: 27 Nov 2020
Date of confirmation of the event: 6 Jan 2021
Reason for notification: Recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: Dec 2014
Manifestation of disease: sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 4
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 26
New outbreaks (26)
Outbreak cluster: Bumbesti Pitic, Gorj (26 outbreaks)
Date of start of the outbreak: 27 Nov 2020
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Backyard
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 262 / 50 / - / - / -

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed in percentages]:
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 19.08 / ** / ** / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
**Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: The outbreak was confirmed within the active surveillance carried out on animals sampled during the period [27 - 30 Nov 2020]. Initially, a high number of positive animals was obtained in the target veterinary concessionary unit Bumbesti Pitic in the serological and PCR tests in December 2020. In order to confirm these results, the re-testing of the animals was disposed. The positive results were confirmed on [6 Jan 2021]. The target veterinary concessionary unit Bumbesti Pitic is situated within the 20 km [approx. 12.4 mi] control zone around the previous bluetongue outbreak (from Valcea county).

Control measures
Measures applied: Movement control inside the country; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; traceability; vector surveillance; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Institute for Diagnosis and Animal Health (national laboratory) / Cattle / Real-time PCR / 6 Jan 2021 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>


[Bluetongue serotype 4 has been reported since July 2020 in the region.

In September 2020 Romania reported an outbreak of Bluetongue, this was also associated to BTV-4. See final report at https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/temp/reports/en_fup_0000037243_20201222_163214.pdf

The immediate notification related to this current event was sent to the OIE on 13 Jan 2021 and can be seen at https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=37594

The list of restriction zones per bluetongue serotype that have been demarcated by the EU Member States can be found in the following table https://ec.europa.eu/food/sites/food/files/animals/docs/ad_control-measures_bt_restrictedzones.pdf (updated 5 Nov 2020).

A map showing the location of the restriction zones can be seen at https://ec.europa.eu/food/sites/food/files/animals/docs/ad_control-measures_bt_restrictedzones-map.jpg (updated 4 Nov 2020). - Mod.CRD


